<br>
The other day I joined a group and I knew 3 of the group members (wizard, cleric, warrior). I had just logged on and was getting oriented to what songs I had memmed and what group members we had. I was looking to see if we had a shaman or enchanter. I saw no shaman but I say an anon int caster I didn't know. <br>
<br>
I said, &quot;Roleb, what class are you?&quot; No response.<br>
<br>
I am still looking at my spell gems and trying to decide which ones I will need and the group starts moving. I run to catch up to them and we have stopped near the entrance to the zone out in Sebilis.<br>
<br>
&quot;Roleb, what class are you?&quot; Still no response.<br>
&quot;Roleb, what class are you?&quot; Still no response.<br>
<br>
A second later. Main tank, &quot;Inc frogluk dar shaman.&quot;<br>
<br>
I look up and see 4 mobs and mez one. Immediately after I mezzed the mob I see a message from Roleb, &quot;MEZZING frogluk dar wizard NOBODY TOUCH IT. &quot; or some such similar message. I realized he was an enchanter and IMMEDIATELY stopped mezzing.<br>
<br>
About 5 seconds later the guy throws a hissy fit. He says, &quot;If the bard mezzes ONE MORE MOB I will start nuking and he can do the mez work.&quot; Right then I realized I have been in say instead of group talk (I had changed to /say to hand in my components for the HS key earlier that day). This explains the misunderstanding.<br>
<br>
I tell him I asked for his class 3 times in say RIGHT NEXT TO HIM and I am sorry if he didn't see it. He continues to call me a liar telling me I should have known when I saw his mez messages. I tell him I stopped mezzing the SECOND I saw it. Can I help it if I mezzed faster then him? Then he rips into bards and basically attacks me calling me a liar. I asked him if he had a problem with bards. I knew he did for some reason and the monk was sending me tells trying to calm me down. The group leader and the cleric tell us to drop it. <br>
<br>
I staying in the group for a bit as I had waited a while to get a group and they were going to D1/D2. After a bit I sent a tell to the enchanter saying, &quot;It seems we got off to a bad start, I would like to apologize for the misunderstanding.&quot; He would have nothing to do with it and outright called me a liar again. I left a bit after that. Roleb is now on my ignore list.<br>
<br>
Did I push an enchanter's hot button without realizing it?  I make a point to try to know who is in my group but they were on the move and this enchanter was anon.  I got the distinct feeling this guy hated bards and didn't trust me.  Is that a common feeling amongst the enchanter community? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ukiriana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiriana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/faces/flowerb2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(5/28/02 6:28:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=77.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.pacifier.com/~godzilla/Kiriana.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Overly sensitive group member</span><hr size=1> That would've earned a spot on my /ignore list.<br>
